1
00:00:07,877 --> 00:00:09,320
Stop sulking already.

2
00:00:09,621 --> 00:00:10,360
Smile.

3
00:00:10,662 --> 00:00:12,200
No matter what your thoughts are,

4
00:00:12,315 --> 00:00:13,600
they have to stop now.

5
00:00:13,787 --> 00:00:17,040
We are only servants. We can only respect him

6
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,760
as one of royal family members.

7
00:00:19,072 --> 00:00:20,800
I saw you enjoy talking to her.

8
00:00:21,158 --> 00:00:22,160
Do you like her?

9
00:00:22,224 --> 00:00:23,840
Dad wanted you to be engaged to Siri.

10
00:00:23,850 --> 00:00:25,720
You know it well that I like Siri.

11
00:00:25,787 --> 00:00:27,720
What's the name of the female vendor in front of the school?

12
00:00:27,788 --> 00:00:28,889
(In unison) Saijai.

13
00:00:28,971 --> 00:00:30,600
She wanted me to give you some snacks.

14
00:00:39,976 --> 00:00:42,320
Who are they? What are they doing in the back?

15
00:02:36,844 --> 00:02:39,120
Who are they? What are they doing in the back?

16
00:02:39,942 --> 00:02:40,943
Your Highness?

17
00:02:43,042 --> 00:02:44,043
Phob?

18
00:02:46,327 --> 00:02:47,580
Hey! Tin!

19
00:02:48,103 --> 00:02:49,044
Tin!

20
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:50,596
How did you take care of him?

21
00:02:50,636 --> 00:02:51,796
Why did you let him get drunk like this?

22
00:02:51,890 --> 00:02:54,356
You're such a big waste, you servant!

23
00:02:59,634 --> 00:03:01,236
Tin! Tin!

24
00:03:03,684 --> 00:03:05,436
You need to take your master back home right now.

25
00:03:06,356 --> 00:03:08,516
And I will tell on you to my dad that you took him to drink.

26
00:03:10,116 --> 00:03:11,356
Go! Just go!

27
00:03:21,642 --> 00:03:22,742
Bring him here. Hurry up!

28
00:03:23,059 --> 00:03:24,916
Watch out! Don't fall!

29
00:03:26,508 --> 00:03:27,509
Here.

30
00:03:34,287 --> 00:03:35,476
Oh my!

31
00:03:35,866 --> 00:03:38,396
Why are you so drunk like this?

32
00:03:38,463 --> 00:03:39,676
Why, Tin?

33
00:03:40,778 --> 00:03:41,779
Oh, you poor thing.

34
00:03:42,804 --> 00:03:44,436
You're done here, you should take a shower.

35
00:03:44,831 --> 00:03:46,236
I will take care of him.

36
00:03:47,129 --> 00:03:48,130
Let's go.

37
00:03:48,810 --> 00:03:49,811
What?

38
00:03:50,495 --> 00:03:52,996
Why don't you let your son take care of him?

39
00:03:53,340 --> 00:03:56,196
That's right. He can help him get changed.

40
00:03:56,386 --> 00:03:59,756
- You're a woman, you can't do it.
- That's right.

41
00:04:00,007 --> 00:04:02,116
- But…
- You should go. Come on.

42
00:04:03,336 --> 00:04:06,450
Phob, take care of him, okay?

43
00:04:06,956 --> 00:04:07,957
We should go.

44
00:04:09,938 --> 00:04:11,596
Nual? Come on.

45
00:04:13,431 --> 00:04:16,436
Phob, you need to clean him well.

46
00:04:17,188 --> 00:04:18,189
Let's go.

47
00:09:03,602 --> 00:09:05,636
♪ The sun ♪

48
00:09:06,119 --> 00:09:09,156
♪ and the ground are far away. ♪

49
00:09:11,162 --> 00:09:13,076
♪ They are too far apart ♪

50
00:09:13,836 --> 00:09:18,316
♪ and they are unreachable. ♪

51
00:09:18,548 --> 00:09:20,356
♪ Even they are destined ♪

52
00:09:21,116 --> 00:09:25,436
♪ not to be together, ♪

53
00:09:26,356 --> 00:09:30,796
♪ I don't believe that I could only have you in my dream. ♪

54
00:09:33,066 --> 00:09:35,116
♪ Will it be possible ♪

55
00:09:35,183 --> 00:09:38,636
♪ for us to be in love? ♪

56
00:09:38,890 --> 00:09:40,836
♪ It seems so far away ♪

57
00:09:40,891 --> 00:09:44,476
♪ that we couldn't see the end. ♪

58
00:09:45,276 --> 00:09:47,716
♪ I won't have a change of heart. ♪

59
00:09:47,736 --> 00:09:49,956
♪ It's just like the sun ♪

60
00:09:50,042 --> 00:09:53,436
♪ that got to meet the ground at dawn. ♪

61
00:09:53,684 --> 00:09:56,876
♪ It was a brief moment but ♪

62
00:09:59,116 --> 00:10:01,196
♪ I will wait to see ♪

63
00:10:01,436 --> 00:10:04,356
♪ the first light of the day. ♪

64
00:10:20,343 --> 00:10:21,344
Phob!

65
00:10:23,207 --> 00:10:26,076
You shouldn't have taken him to go partying this late.

66
00:10:27,116 --> 00:10:28,356
I tried to stop him.

67
00:10:28,796 --> 00:10:29,797
Stop talking back to me.

68
00:10:33,314 --> 00:10:34,436
You need to pack up

69
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:37,396
you need to visit your aunt in Ayutthaya with me in two days.

70
00:12:12,138 --> 00:12:13,139
Phob.

71
00:12:18,948 --> 00:12:21,796
Nual said that you will visit your relatives in Ayutthaya, right?

72
00:12:23,231 --> 00:12:24,232
That's right, Your Highness.

73
00:12:25,316 --> 00:12:26,636
For how many days?

74
00:12:27,935 --> 00:12:30,516
A few days, I guess.

75
00:12:39,596 --> 00:12:42,436
- About last night…
- If there is nothing else,

76
00:12:42,812 --> 00:12:44,676
I really need to pack my stuff, Your Highness.

77
00:12:45,319 --> 00:12:46,320
Phob!

78
00:12:47,236 --> 00:12:48,237
I…

79
00:12:48,516 --> 00:12:49,756
There you are.

80
00:12:53,362 --> 00:12:54,363
Actually,

81
00:12:54,850 --> 00:12:56,556
Princess Ruethaisiri is here to see you.

82
00:12:57,234 --> 00:12:58,796
She is talking to your grandma right now.

83
00:12:59,959 --> 00:13:00,960
Got it.

84
00:13:20,612 --> 00:13:23,316
Ruethaisiri just learned how to bake a cake

85
00:13:23,508 --> 00:13:25,196
and she's kind enough to share some to us.

86
00:13:27,516 --> 00:13:29,196
You should try, honey.

87
00:13:30,236 --> 00:13:32,396
Please come and sit with me.

88
00:13:35,162 --> 00:13:36,636
Thank you so much.

89
00:13:37,770 --> 00:13:38,916
Oh my goodness,

90
00:13:39,044 --> 00:13:41,356
the cake looks so good

91
00:13:42,228 --> 00:13:44,156
just like the giver.

92
00:13:44,747 --> 00:13:47,716
It's just like a match made in heaven.

93
00:13:49,386 --> 00:13:51,916
Stop talking already, come on.

94
00:13:59,642 --> 00:14:01,836
You don't want to marry me, do you?

95
00:14:04,735 --> 00:14:07,756
Why did you bring it up?

96
00:14:09,236 --> 00:14:12,156
You've changed since you heard about our engagement.

97
00:14:13,223 --> 00:14:15,476
It seems like you're not comfortable to talk to me.

98
00:14:17,575 --> 00:14:18,576
I…

99
00:14:18,706 --> 00:14:20,236
I still like you the same.

100
00:14:21,556 --> 00:14:22,557
But…

101
00:14:22,815 --> 00:14:25,076
- I just..
- You were forced, weren't you?

102
00:14:31,316 --> 00:14:33,596
I see you as a sister.

103
00:14:34,601 --> 00:14:37,236
When I learned that we needed to get married, I was shocked.

104
00:14:38,588 --> 00:14:39,796
I understand you completely.

105
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:42,236
We're the 'suitable' couple.

106
00:14:43,446 --> 00:14:46,036
My dad designated my whole entire life.

107
00:14:47,596 --> 00:14:49,676
If we don’t come with titles,

108
00:14:49,919 --> 00:14:52,636
perhaps we could have more freedom in our lives.

109
00:14:54,247 --> 00:14:57,016
You don't want to get married either?

110
00:14:58,876 --> 00:15:00,356
Can we say no to our parents?

111
00:15:02,671 --> 00:15:03,672
What about this?

112
00:15:04,266 --> 00:15:06,036
I will ask my father

113
00:15:06,138 --> 00:15:07,516
to postpone the wedding.

114
00:15:08,506 --> 00:15:09,876
When I come back from the UK,

115
00:15:09,967 --> 00:15:11,676
we can talk about it again.

116
00:15:12,135 --> 00:15:14,396
We should be grown enough by then,

117
00:15:15,095 --> 00:15:17,036
and we need to be firm when we tell the parents

118
00:15:17,116 --> 00:15:19,076
that we don't like each other like that.

119
00:15:19,836 --> 00:15:22,516
I think our fathers should understand.

120
00:15:24,116 --> 00:15:25,117
Good idea.

121
00:16:07,356 --> 00:16:09,357
[We need to talk.]

122
00:16:32,308 --> 00:16:33,447
You called me here,

123
00:16:34,748 --> 00:16:36,156
what can I do for you?

124
00:16:38,993 --> 00:16:39,994
We need to talk.

125
00:16:43,402 --> 00:16:44,403
Can we talk tomorrow?

126
00:16:45,599 --> 00:16:46,600
It's getting late

127
00:16:47,956 --> 00:16:48,957
and it is inappropriate.

128
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:52,196
What do you mean by 'inappropriate'?

129
00:16:54,159 --> 00:16:55,716
We used to sneak out here to hang out all the time.

130
00:16:58,426 --> 00:16:59,556
That was before this.

131
00:17:02,698 --> 00:17:03,699
Right now,

132
00:17:05,356 --> 00:17:06,476
it is not the same anymore.

133
00:17:07,956 --> 00:17:09,036
What is not the same?

134
00:17:11,260 --> 00:17:12,396
I am still the same.

135
00:17:17,567 --> 00:17:19,036
Is it you

136
00:17:20,156 --> 00:17:21,157
who changed?

137
00:17:28,133 --> 00:17:29,396
At the bar last night,

138
00:17:29,906 --> 00:17:31,907
you still haven't told me

139
00:17:31,936 --> 00:17:32,937
why you tried to avoid me?

140
00:17:35,996 --> 00:17:37,356
Please let it go, don't mind me.

141
00:17:37,596 --> 00:17:38,756
Of course, I do.

142
00:17:40,770 --> 00:17:42,316
Phob, I will leave for the UK soon,

143
00:17:42,524 --> 00:17:45,276
you wish me to leave when things are uncleared like this?

144
00:17:56,906 --> 00:17:57,907
Perhaps,

145
00:17:59,322 --> 00:18:00,676
it is better that way.

146
00:18:04,244 --> 00:18:05,456
Excuse me.

147
00:18:05,839 --> 00:18:06,840
Coward!

148
00:18:10,868 --> 00:18:12,236
You're not Phob that I used to know.

149
00:18:20,455 --> 00:18:21,516
Is this what you want?

150
00:18:26,514 --> 00:18:28,196
You kissed other and now you're acting like this.

151
00:18:44,703 --> 00:18:45,956
I know what happened last night.

152
00:18:51,236 --> 00:18:52,637
You kissed me

153
00:18:54,476 --> 00:18:55,477
and I knew it.

154
00:19:27,850 --> 00:19:28,851
I'm sorry.

155
00:19:29,780 --> 00:19:32,316
I'm sorry, it was an accident.

156
00:19:33,796 --> 00:19:34,797
An accident?

157
00:19:36,527 --> 00:19:37,528
What do you mean?

158
00:19:38,479 --> 00:19:40,116
You still haven't told me the truth.

159
00:19:41,098 --> 00:19:42,276
What do you want me to say?

160
00:19:43,247 --> 00:19:45,636
You want me to say that a servant took advantage of his master?

161
00:19:48,151 --> 00:19:49,916
That I didn't know my place?

162
00:19:51,554 --> 00:19:53,156
That I thought of you in inappropriate way?

163
00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:56,276
So that you can be disgusted by me even more?

164
00:20:31,388 --> 00:20:33,756
Do you still think that you're disgusting to me?

165
00:20:40,655 --> 00:20:42,596
♪ The sun ♪

166
00:20:43,332 --> 00:20:46,156
♪ and the ground are far away. ♪

167
00:20:48,316 --> 00:20:49,956
♪ They are too far apart ♪

168
00:20:50,876 --> 00:20:55,116
♪ and they are unreachable. ♪

169
00:20:55,676 --> 00:20:57,336
♪ Even they are destined ♪

170
00:20:58,236 --> 00:21:02,356
♪ not to be together, ♪

171
00:21:02,796 --> 00:21:04,556
I'm not dreaming, am I?

172
00:21:06,296 --> 00:21:07,356
You're dreaming

173
00:21:10,559 --> 00:21:11,636
and you will wake up soon.

174
00:21:22,658 --> 00:21:23,659
If this is a dream,

175
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:26,876
then I want to stay in my dream forever.

176
00:21:29,594 --> 00:21:30,876
I don't want to wake up.

177
00:21:32,015 --> 00:21:34,196
Then you should keep on dreaming like this.

178
00:21:34,383 --> 00:21:36,556
♪ It seems so far away ♪

179
00:21:36,796 --> 00:21:39,276
♪ that we couldn't see the end. ♪

180
00:21:40,599 --> 00:21:42,956
♪ I won't have a change of heart. ♪

181
00:21:43,036 --> 00:21:45,037
♪ It's just like the sun ♪

182
00:21:45,356 --> 00:21:46,357
But soon

183
00:21:48,596 --> 00:21:49,716
you will study abroad.

184
00:21:52,242 --> 00:21:53,243
So what?

185
00:21:55,356 --> 00:21:57,636
Are you saying that you won't

186
00:21:58,295 --> 00:21:59,396
wait for me when I study in the UK?

187
00:22:04,423 --> 00:22:06,596
I don't care if it will be months, or years,

188
00:22:07,476 --> 00:22:08,477
or all my life,

189
00:22:10,796 --> 00:22:12,996
I will wait for you and you only.

190
00:22:15,036 --> 00:22:17,156
No matter what,

191
00:22:17,876 --> 00:22:18,877
I will forever

192
00:22:19,956 --> 00:22:20,957
be your Phob.

193
00:22:27,482 --> 00:22:28,916
Aren't you the cutest?

194
00:22:54,252 --> 00:22:55,253
I love you.

195
00:22:58,364 --> 00:22:59,596
I love you, too, Your Highness.

196
00:23:18,956 --> 00:23:20,916
It's late, where have you been?

197
00:23:22,423 --> 00:23:25,036
I couldn't sleep so I went out to get some fresh air.

198
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:53,196
We're here to say goodbye, Your Highness.

199
00:23:55,602 --> 00:23:57,716
We will visit our relatives in Ayutthaya

200
00:23:57,847 --> 00:23:59,116
for a couple days.

201
00:23:59,842 --> 00:24:00,843
You should go

202
00:24:01,068 --> 00:24:03,916
and take care of your relatives until they get better,

203
00:24:04,130 --> 00:24:05,676
then you can come back.

204
00:24:10,999 --> 00:24:13,796
Phob, take this.

205
00:24:24,711 --> 00:24:25,836
Thank you, Your Highness.

206
00:24:26,279 --> 00:24:29,436
You should be gone forever.

207
00:24:31,399 --> 00:24:33,236
You have such a foul mouth.

208
00:24:33,351 --> 00:24:35,636
If you're quiet, nobody would think that you're a mute.

209
00:24:52,452 --> 00:24:53,453
Let's go, Phob.

210
00:24:59,015 --> 00:25:01,876
I wish you two a safe trip.

211
00:25:30,988 --> 00:25:31,989
Come in.

212
00:25:39,076 --> 00:25:40,077
What is it, Tin?

213
00:25:42,351 --> 00:25:43,352
About…

214
00:25:43,727 --> 00:25:45,940
my study in the UK.

215
00:25:47,631 --> 00:25:49,316
What about it? Is there a problem?

216
00:25:50,556 --> 00:25:52,276
Everything is fine.

217
00:25:54,327 --> 00:25:56,796
But I need to ask you a favor.

218
00:26:00,596 --> 00:26:02,397
Is it possible

219
00:26:03,263 --> 00:26:05,716
that Phob could go to the UK with me?

220
00:26:10,516 --> 00:26:13,156
You two can't be apart, can you?

221
00:26:16,879 --> 00:26:18,975
Actually, I think that

222
00:26:19,402 --> 00:26:20,686
Phob is a bright student.

223
00:26:22,458 --> 00:26:25,359
If any of the departments issue scholarships to study in the UK,

224
00:26:26,164 --> 00:26:28,236
I think Phob should join the test.

225
00:26:28,847 --> 00:26:30,476
He could be there to take care of you.

226
00:26:33,196 --> 00:26:34,636
Thank you, Dad.

227
00:26:43,570 --> 00:26:45,716
He wanted Phob to go to the UK with him?

228
00:26:54,394 --> 00:26:55,436
What is going on?

229
00:26:56,682 --> 00:26:59,536
Why did you ask Dad to send Phob to the UK with you?

230
00:26:59,890 --> 00:27:01,116
You should have asked for me.

231
00:27:02,060 --> 00:27:03,061
Oh, come on.

232
00:27:03,490 --> 00:27:06,876
Honestly, you should focus on passing the tests here first.

233
00:27:09,244 --> 00:27:10,396
Are you underestimating me?

234
00:27:12,748 --> 00:27:14,076
You see him better than me?

235
00:27:14,647 --> 00:27:16,516
You only focus on him…

236
00:27:22,476 --> 00:27:23,477
I just figure it out.

237
00:27:25,580 --> 00:27:26,581
What are you talking about?

238
00:27:28,478 --> 00:27:30,996
I saw it the other night

239
00:27:31,756 --> 00:27:32,876
in the back of the bar.

240
00:27:33,527 --> 00:27:34,528
I know what you did.

241
00:27:39,175 --> 00:27:40,676
What did you see?

242
00:27:51,530 --> 00:27:53,316
You're completely drunk.

243
00:27:54,884 --> 00:27:55,845
Right?

244
00:27:55,850 --> 00:27:58,476
So you can Phob can go clubbing all the time?

245
00:27:59,276 --> 00:28:00,377
Stop talking nonsense already.

246
00:28:09,943 --> 00:28:11,276
Why did he act so surprised like that?

247
00:28:14,044 --> 00:28:15,276
They're so weird.

248
00:28:24,876 --> 00:28:25,877
[Ayutthaya]

249
00:28:30,786 --> 00:28:32,236
Thank you so much, Nual.

250
00:28:32,636 --> 00:28:35,236
Actually, I'm not feeling bad at all.

251
00:28:35,716 --> 00:28:38,316
You and Phob shouldn't come all the way here.

252
00:28:39,396 --> 00:28:40,636
It's okay, Cham.

253
00:28:40,996 --> 00:28:42,940
We should be on vacation once in a while.

254
00:28:44,636 --> 00:28:46,396
Well, I need to rest.

255
00:28:46,956 --> 00:28:48,116
Make yourself at home.

256
00:28:58,836 --> 00:28:59,837
Mom?

257
00:29:00,378 --> 00:29:02,036
Aunt Cham looks fine to me.

258
00:29:03,379 --> 00:29:04,636
Should we go back now?

259
00:29:05,463 --> 00:29:06,996
I think we should stay for a while.

260
00:29:07,556 --> 00:29:08,636
We don't need to rush back.

261
00:29:08,967 --> 00:29:10,226
What? Mom!

262
00:29:14,543 --> 00:29:15,716
What are you talking about?

263
00:29:16,298 --> 00:29:18,356
You're moving to Ayutthaya?

264
00:29:18,612 --> 00:29:19,613
Yes, Your Highness.

265
00:29:20,298 --> 00:29:23,156
My relatives can help us.

266
00:29:24,087 --> 00:29:25,088
I think

267
00:29:25,932 --> 00:29:27,516
I will find something to sell

268
00:29:28,018 --> 00:29:30,556
and I can take care of my sick relatives.

269
00:29:31,890 --> 00:29:33,596
Why is it so sudden?

270
00:29:34,092 --> 00:29:35,271
Is everything okay?

271
00:29:35,570 --> 00:29:38,476
That's right. Or you think that

272
00:29:38,676 --> 00:29:40,796
we don't take good care of you?

273
00:29:40,999 --> 00:29:44,276
You can tell me if something is bothering you.

274
00:29:46,350 --> 00:29:47,356
Everything is fine, Your Highness.

275
00:29:48,399 --> 00:29:50,356
I can be who I am

276
00:29:51,476 --> 00:29:52,831
because of this place.

277
00:29:53,866 --> 00:29:56,967
I don't know how to

278
00:29:57,828 --> 00:29:59,236
pay back for your kindness.

279
00:30:00,516 --> 00:30:03,956
It's just that I need to take care of my sick relatives.

280
00:30:05,463 --> 00:30:06,464
And that's all.

281
00:30:12,306 --> 00:30:14,407
Nual? What about Phob?

282
00:30:18,063 --> 00:30:19,596
He will stay with me.

283
00:30:22,970 --> 00:30:24,036
He won't be back.

284
00:30:30,679 --> 00:30:32,594
Nual! Nual!

285
00:30:36,876 --> 00:30:37,956
My dad told me that

286
00:30:38,415 --> 00:30:40,996
he wants Phob to join the test for a scholarship to study in the UK with me.

287
00:30:42,484 --> 00:30:43,716
Please let him go with me.

288
00:30:48,356 --> 00:30:49,357
Your Highness.

289
00:30:51,138 --> 00:30:52,596
I'm forever grateful

290
00:30:54,036 --> 00:30:56,316
for your kindness to both of us.

291
00:30:57,378 --> 00:30:58,379
But…

292
00:30:59,090 --> 00:31:00,596
Phob has to stay here with me.

293
00:31:02,396 --> 00:31:04,156
You're about to get in a way of his entire future.

294
00:31:06,087 --> 00:31:08,276
You know that he's a fast learner and a bright student.

295
00:31:09,266 --> 00:31:12,116
You know that he deserves better education.

296
00:31:12,748 --> 00:31:13,796
I know it well.

297
00:31:16,796 --> 00:31:18,476
But this is the only way…

298
00:31:19,570 --> 00:31:20,596
to protect him

299
00:31:21,554 --> 00:31:22,555
and…

300
00:31:23,336 --> 00:31:25,436
to protect your honor.

301
00:31:27,346 --> 00:31:28,347
What are you talking about?

302
00:31:30,892 --> 00:31:31,893
Who would hurt Phob?

303
00:31:33,228 --> 00:31:36,716
What did my honor have anything to do with it?

304
00:31:49,864 --> 00:31:51,116
Your Highness,

305
00:31:52,722 --> 00:31:53,796
please trust me.

306
00:31:57,036 --> 00:31:58,956
This is for the best.

307
00:32:39,823 --> 00:32:41,836
♪ The sun ♪

308
00:32:42,420 --> 00:32:45,396
♪ and the ground are far away. ♪

309
00:32:47,396 --> 00:32:49,356
♪ They are too far apart ♪

310
00:32:51,794 --> 00:32:53,356
- Do you know what it is?
- Like what?

311
00:32:53,778 --> 00:32:54,779
Like Ngoh!

312
00:32:55,596 --> 00:32:57,556
You saw me as an ugly and dirty-looking guy, didn't you?

313
00:32:57,927 --> 00:33:01,036
I mean you look like Ngoh when he shows his real self.

314
00:33:01,916 --> 00:33:04,556
Ngoh's skin is covered with gold.

315
00:33:07,791 --> 00:33:08,876
But I'm just a servant,

316
00:33:10,468 --> 00:33:11,856
I am nothing like him.

317
00:33:13,070 --> 00:33:16,036
Nobody would toss me a garland

318
00:33:16,596 --> 00:33:17,597
like she did to him.

319
00:33:18,658 --> 00:33:19,659
No garland

320
00:33:20,231 --> 00:33:22,356
but you can have the cotton rose.

321
00:33:23,756 --> 00:33:25,076
So it means that

322
00:33:28,316 --> 00:33:31,556
you choose me, right?

323
00:33:40,900 --> 00:33:42,836
Can you help me

324
00:33:42,901 --> 00:33:45,276
- find a rental house in the area?
- Sure.

325
00:33:46,202 --> 00:33:48,203
Are you sure about moving back here?

326
00:33:48,628 --> 00:33:50,356
You're not staying in the palace anymore?

327
00:33:51,210 --> 00:33:53,036
- Or your masters…?
- All of them

328
00:33:53,156 --> 00:33:54,757
are so kind to me and my son.

329
00:33:55,375 --> 00:33:56,376
That's why

330
00:33:56,906 --> 00:33:58,956
we shouldn't go back there.

331
00:34:00,300 --> 00:34:01,301
What did you just say?

332
00:34:02,332 --> 00:34:03,516
We're not going back to the palace?

333
00:34:14,402 --> 00:34:16,156
Mom! Mom!

334
00:34:17,276 --> 00:34:19,396
What do you mean by us not going back to the palace?

335
00:34:19,716 --> 00:34:22,196
You heard what I said. We will stay here.

336
00:34:22,530 --> 00:34:24,596
- You can't go back.
- Why is that?

337
00:34:24,876 --> 00:34:26,114
You should ask yourself that.

338
00:34:26,498 --> 00:34:27,499
What did I do?

339
00:34:34,300 --> 00:34:35,916
That night, under a cotton rose tree,

340
00:34:37,324 --> 00:34:38,525
I saw you

341
00:34:40,396 --> 00:34:41,556
and Prince Tinnakorn.

342
00:34:48,340 --> 00:34:49,341
If you saw us,

343
00:34:50,108 --> 00:34:51,196
then you would know

344
00:34:52,348 --> 00:34:54,336
that we shared the same feeling.

345
00:34:55,079 --> 00:34:57,116
Why do you have to stop people who are in love?

346
00:34:57,532 --> 00:35:00,543
Didn't you hear what you just said?

347
00:35:00,612 --> 00:35:01,676
It is the truth.

348
00:35:02,276 --> 00:35:03,516
I am speaking the truth.

349
00:35:04,396 --> 00:35:07,756
The prince and I, we are in love.

350
00:35:08,916 --> 00:35:10,836
You can't love him like that.

351
00:35:14,343 --> 00:35:16,476
You should revere him.

352
00:35:16,956 --> 00:35:19,396
- Because he is your master.
- So what?

353
00:35:19,952 --> 00:35:21,596
I can revere him

354
00:35:22,319 --> 00:35:24,716
and let him be my lover. Can't I do that?

355
00:35:24,746 --> 00:35:27,636
- You're about to ruin his reputation.
- Ruin because of what?

356
00:35:28,527 --> 00:35:30,196
Because I am a man?

357
00:35:30,372 --> 00:35:32,436
Or because I am a servant and he is my master?

358
00:35:32,490 --> 00:35:33,786
Both of them.

359
00:35:35,092 --> 00:35:36,556
You should have known

360
00:35:37,183 --> 00:35:38,996
that the sky is high and the ground is low.

361
00:35:39,716 --> 00:35:42,076
You shouldn't dragged the sky to stoop to the ground level.

362
00:35:44,876 --> 00:35:45,877
Mom,

363
00:35:46,896 --> 00:35:49,986
nobody is higher or lower when it's about love.

364
00:35:50,514 --> 00:35:52,036
It is about our hearts.

365
00:35:55,596 --> 00:35:56,956
If the sky and the ground got in my way,

366
00:35:57,522 --> 00:35:59,556
if to be a master and a servant got in my way,

367
00:36:00,034 --> 00:36:01,676
I will destroy them all.

368
00:36:28,956 --> 00:36:29,957
Phob!

369
00:36:32,674 --> 00:36:33,675
Phob!

370
00:36:36,596 --> 00:36:37,597
Phob!

371
00:36:39,116 --> 00:36:40,636
Phob! Come back here.

372
00:37:40,178 --> 00:37:41,179
Phob!

373
00:38:03,972 --> 00:38:06,356
Co..Colo…

374
00:38:07,391 --> 00:38:09,316
nel…means...

375
00:38:11,204 --> 00:38:12,205
a senior commissioned military officer.

376
00:38:18,308 --> 00:38:19,309
Did I get it right?

377
00:38:23,287 --> 00:38:27,036
Damn it! I enunciated it wrong.

378
00:38:27,488 --> 00:38:30,396
Why does it write like that and enuciate like that?

379
00:38:33,052 --> 00:38:34,436
Damn you rain! Stop raining already.

380
00:38:42,336 --> 00:38:43,337
Is that…

381
00:38:43,959 --> 00:38:44,960
Phob?

382
00:38:47,522 --> 00:38:48,523
Tin?

383
00:38:58,412 --> 00:38:59,413
Where are they going?

384
00:39:09,472 --> 00:39:11,396
Didn't I tell you to study?

385
00:39:11,804 --> 00:39:13,548
I just saw Phob

386
00:39:14,076 --> 00:39:15,676
and Tin running to the main's quarters.

387
00:39:16,110 --> 00:39:18,596
- So I was about to…
- You need to go back to your room to study.

388
00:39:46,383 --> 00:39:47,384
Phob!

389
00:39:48,927 --> 00:39:50,556
I thought that I would never see you again.

390
00:39:52,336 --> 00:39:53,596
What happened?

391
00:39:53,700 --> 00:39:55,436
Why both of you need to move out?

392
00:39:56,401 --> 00:39:57,436
I don't get it.

393
00:39:59,036 --> 00:40:00,037
Your Highness,

394
00:40:02,076 --> 00:40:03,077
my mom found out about it.

395
00:40:04,772 --> 00:40:06,036
She knows about us.

396
00:40:06,436 --> 00:40:07,437
What did you just say?

397
00:40:11,636 --> 00:40:14,237
Is it the reason why she wanted you to move out?

398
00:40:16,356 --> 00:40:18,036
What should we do?

399
00:40:22,250 --> 00:40:23,596
Don't you worry.

400
00:40:25,434 --> 00:40:28,716
I will not let anything to get in our way.

401
00:40:29,836 --> 00:40:31,196
I will not give up

402
00:40:32,372 --> 00:40:33,876
and you can't give up either.

403
00:40:39,428 --> 00:40:41,866
Phob, I talked to my dad about going to the UK.

404
00:40:42,922 --> 00:40:45,376
He said that you can join the scholarship's test and follow me.

405
00:40:46,436 --> 00:40:48,356
If you pass the test, you will join me.

406
00:40:49,516 --> 00:40:50,596
We can study abroad together.

407
00:40:51,356 --> 00:40:53,276
- Really?
- Yeah.

408
00:40:54,316 --> 00:40:55,317
We will go there together.

409
00:41:08,111 --> 00:41:09,112
Phob,

410
00:41:10,276 --> 00:41:12,116
you are soaking.

411
00:41:12,676 --> 00:41:13,956
I think you should get changed.

412
00:41:14,714 --> 00:41:17,276
And I will bring you to meet my dad tomorrow.

413
00:41:18,236 --> 00:41:19,836
He will talk to Nual for you.

414
00:41:20,356 --> 00:41:22,156
I don't think Nual would disagree with him.

415
00:41:28,593 --> 00:41:29,594
What is it?

416
00:41:31,111 --> 00:41:32,112
You know what?

417
00:41:33,671 --> 00:41:35,356
I thought that I would never see you again.

418
00:41:37,935 --> 00:41:40,436
Well, you're seeing me now.

419
00:41:41,924 --> 00:41:43,276
Are you still not satisfied?

420
00:41:48,258 --> 00:41:50,076
What if I say that I'm not yet satisfied?

421
00:41:55,063 --> 00:41:57,996
So what do you want me to do?

422
00:41:58,064 --> 00:41:59,065
To satisfy you?

423
00:45:35,682 --> 00:45:38,156
It's late and it's pouring rain.

424
00:45:38,676 --> 00:45:39,677
What are they doing?

425
00:45:40,877 --> 00:45:41,878
Where are you going?

426
00:45:44,402 --> 00:45:45,476
Dad?

427
00:45:49,036 --> 00:45:50,116
What are you doing here?

428
00:45:50,988 --> 00:45:52,876
I really saw Phob.

429
00:45:53,143 --> 00:45:55,436
Tin is with him, too. I don't know what they are up to.

430
00:45:57,036 --> 00:45:58,796
Are you going back to study? Nicely?

431
00:46:00,142 --> 00:46:01,143
But Dad?

432
00:46:03,376 --> 00:46:04,377
Yes.

433
00:46:45,398 --> 00:46:46,399
Your Highness!

434
00:46:46,619 --> 00:46:47,620
Dad!

435
00:47:10,011 --> 00:47:13,600
- What happened between Phob and I ended that night.
- Of course, I trust you.

436
00:47:13,758 --> 00:47:15,000
It's the other that I don't trust.

437
00:47:15,086 --> 00:47:17,200
Not fair! Siam will be in big trouble.

438
00:47:17,261 --> 00:47:20,600
People started to question whom the government is ruling for.

439
00:47:20,712 --> 00:47:22,840
You used to live in Varakulvatin Palace, didn't you?

440
00:47:23,611 --> 00:47:26,512
We should hurry up and follow the plan as we discussed.

441
00:47:26,560 --> 00:47:28,040
Tin, I think that is Phob.

